                <div class="about-text">
                    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Program Overview</h2>
                    <p>
                        This program offers specialized training for philologists and researchers in modern digital methods for studying language evolution. It combines traditional linguistic analysis with computational tools, fully adopting the <strong>Open Access</strong> philosophy.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Target Audience:</strong> Open to philologists of all languages (Classics, Byzantine, Modern Greek, English, German, French, Spanish, Italian, etc.), educators interested in digital methods, linguistics graduate students, digital humanities researchers, and language technology professionals.
                    </p>
                    <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 1.5rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--primary); margin-top: 2rem;">
